oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Netting much attention, from the Nashville Times, 1940
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A captioned photo from the Nashville Times (1940), about model Jane Hanse “netting much attention … models a fetching white terry cloth cape, which sets off the crocheted bathing suit of unusual design she has selected. White accessories go with it.” Forms part of the Nashville Times newspaper collection. 1 digital photo.
